passages.text: Good ARR Recovery Offs by Lack of Upside with Outlook

SentinelOne delivered substantially better than expected ARR, but lack of flow through to full year guidance leaves us cautious. SentinelOne's results for 2Q were better than expected as ARR rebounded with growth of \(24\%\) y/y to over \(\) 1bn. Performance was supported by healthy logo adds as well as expansion with existing customers with increased adoption of SIEM, Purple AI, and CNAPP in addition to broader platform adoption. Purple AI traction was notable in particular, with greater than \(30\%\) license attach rates in the quarter. The company also followed the lead of several of its Security peers with the launch of its SentinelOne Flex pricing model this quarter. In spite of much better traction across the platform for the quarter, full year revenue guidance was left relatively unchanged (increased by just \(\) 2\mathrm{mm}$ at the bottom end and \(\) 1\mathrm{mm}$ at the top vs a \(\sim\) 1bn run rate), which will likely give investors pause considering the degree of implied conservatism that remains embedded in the outlook. The announced acquisition of Prompt in the quarter is expected to have an immaterial impact to revenue growth this year, but we think it will provide another point of scrutiny with regard to lack of upward guidance revision. Operating margin of just over \(2\%\) was slightly better than expected for the quarter while operating margin guidance for the full year was trimmed to account for an expected 80bp headwind attributable to the Prompt deal. SentinelOne is still one of the faster- growing vendors within our coverage universe, but it also remains at an earlier stage of inflection toward profitability and FCF, which we expect will translate into less fundamental valuation support nearterm. We continue to see potential for growth to reaccelerate but we think the company will need to string together several quarters of consistently better execution, following recent quarters of disappointment, in order to be rewarded with a better multiple. We remain Neutral rated as we update our estimates for current period results and outlook.

Good ARR recovery with profitability. The company reported 2Q Net New ARR of \(\) 52.9\mathrm{mm}$ (growth of \(20\%\) y/y), above street expectations of \(\) 37.3\mathrm{mm}\(Overall ARR crossed the\) \ \(1\mathrm{bn}\) threshold with 2Q ARR of \(\) 1,001\mathrm{mm}\(reflecting growth of\)24\%\(y/y, relatively in - line with growth in 1Q26. The company reported better than expected 2Q adjusted operating income of\) \ \(5.4\mathrm{mm}\) , reflecting a margin of \(2.2\%\) . Although 2Q FCF of \(\) 7.1\mathrm{mm}\(fell short of consensus estimates, the company reiterated that Free Cash Flow for FY26 is expected to end up a few points above adjusted operating margin.

Continued platform traction. SentinelOne continued to see success with platform solutions across Endpoint, Cloud, Data, and AI. Non- endpoint solutions once again represented approximately half of quarterly bookings. Purple AI achieved triple- digit y/y growth in quarterly bookings

with over \(30\%\) attach rates to licenses sold in 20. Data solutions saw healthy contribution to total bookings with increasing adoption of large enterprises. Customers with ARR of more than \(\) 100k\(grew\) 23\% \(y / y\) to 1,5 up from 1,459 in 1Q. As noted above, the company also launched SentinelOne \(x\) during the quarter, a flexible licensing model that gives organizations the agility to manage entitlements and seamlessly deploy new platform capabilities.

- 2Q strength not reflected in guidance. The company guided to 3Q revenue of \(\) 256m\(m, in-line with consensus expectations of\) \ \(255.6m\) , and an adjusted operating income margin of \(4\%\) . The implied midpoint of FY26 revenue guidance of \(\) 1,000m\(remains relatively unchanged, with an increase of just\) \ \(1m\) at the top-end. Better than consensus ARR performance in 2Q is not reflected in the 2H26 implied guidance as the company continues to take a measured approach due to variability in the timing of larger deals, overall macro and Federal environment.

- Contribution from Prompt Security. The purchase price for Prompt Security was approximately \(\) 180m\(. It is expected to have minimal revenue and ARR contribution in FY26 and 80bps operating margin impact for the full year. The management noted that the acquisition enhances the Singularity platform with the ability to monitor, govern and control GenAI usage across the enterprise which will help solidify the company's position as an AI Security company.

- Revamped partner program. SentinelOne launched PartnerOne, a new program for MSSPs, incident responders, VARs, and technology partners in Q1. It features a streamlined tiering structure, performance-based incentives, and customized enablement resources. The launch of PartnerOne could enable the company to reach more customers and increase the flexibility of the platform. The management noted that they continue to expand and deepen engagements with partners.

Emerging product traction. Seeing more contribution from Data, Cloud, and AI security solutions could support growth longer term. Strategic investment. SentinelOne can provide strategic value to others in the industry. Profitability and FCF. Improving profitability/FCF could provide better levels of valuation support.

Competition. SentinelOne faces competition primarily from market leaders in the EPP segment and next- gen XDR leaders. As well, as SentinelOne expands into adjacent markets, we also expect the company could face competition from next- gen companies in these respective segments that already have dominant presence in these markets and strong customer relationships. Sustainability of growth. As the company continues to scale, we consider that similar levels of growth may not be sustainable in the future. Innovation and platform/module expansion will be critical as the company continues to expand. Execution risk. The company has a history of poor execution.
SentinelOne (Neutral; Price Target: \(19.00\) )

SentinelOne has established itself as a best- of- breed next- generation EDR leader whose disruptive platform has enabled it to grow revenue and ARR at high rates. We believe the company is prudently taking action to focus costs in order to achieve its goal of profitability. In our opinion, the company is well positioned to deliver strong margin expansion (both gross and operating) and remains well positioned to continue to take Endpoint market share, expand into adjacent markets, and deliver strong growth with improving fundamentals.

Our Dec 2026 price target of \(\) 19\(unchanged) is derived from a 4.7x EV / CY26E Sales multiple (Sales of\) \ \(1211\) mn for CY26). There is no change in our price target methodology as our price target was previously derived from implied CY26 multiples. The \(4.7x Sales multiple is at a \~3x turn discount to the median of our coverage universe.
